WEBVTT

00:00.016 --> 00:01.366
<i>Previously on</i> Riverdale...

00:01.386 --> 00:03.116
<i>I burned your drugs
and equipment.</i>

00:03.196 --> 00:05.366
You owe me $75,000, Veronica.

00:05.446 --> 00:08.666
Now my buyer is coming,
and they are gonna want blood.

00:08.736 --> 00:11.706
- Here's your money.
- Then we'll figure out a payment plan for the rest.

00:11.716 --> 00:13.376
- What's this?
- A gang.

00:13.386 --> 00:15.336
The Pretty Poisons.

00:15.666 --> 00:18.256
Is this gang mine, or yours?

00:18.336 --> 00:20.546
It's... yours.

00:20.626 --> 00:22.256
Start by quitting the speakeasy.

00:22.336 --> 00:24.926
Forget about protecting
Lodge's daughter.

00:25.006 --> 00:28.306
If you don't get your house in order,
the Serpents' little piece in the pie

00:28.316 --> 00:30.436
is gonna get smaller.
You need numbers.

00:30.446 --> 00:33.476
Are you Kurtz?
If you and your Gargoyles join my gang,

00:33.486 --> 00:36.276
I can promise you immunity
from the sheriff's office.

00:36.346 --> 00:38.656
You are all just sacrifices
waiting to be made.

00:38.736 --> 00:41.446
This symbol the Warden branded on
Archie's hip, what does it mean?

00:41.526 --> 00:42.476
Sacrifice.

00:42.556 --> 00:44.076
It meant that Archie had to die.

00:44.146 --> 00:46.576
Gargoyles aren't the answer.
I don't want 'em anywhere near us.

00:46.656 --> 00:48.486
I did what you couldn't.

00:48.566 --> 00:51.006
- This is a bad idea. -I know you guys
will find a way to work together.

00:51.086 --> 00:53.626
<i>After what happened with
Moose, and him leaving town,</i>

00:53.696 --> 00:55.246
<i>Evelyn started talking to me.</i>

00:55.316 --> 00:57.846
Tell me you're not thinking
about actually joining the Farm.

00:57.926 --> 01:02.136
We are gathered here tonight to
celebrate the baptizing of Alice Smith.

01:02.206 --> 01:03.796
They tried to kill you, Mom.

01:03.876 --> 01:07.476
No, I saw it. My destiny.
I'm gonna sell this house.

01:07.546 --> 01:09.236
We're gonna all be together.

01:17.726 --> 01:19.326
<i>Mid century colonial,</i>

01:20.916 --> 01:23.166
<i>on a quite elm-lined street.</i>

01:24.786 --> 01:26.336
<i>Three bedrooms, four baths.</i>

01:27.236 --> 01:29.656
<i>Perfect for families.</i>

01:29.736 --> 01:32.176
<i>Plenty of storage,
and generous closet space...</i>

01:33.546 --> 01:36.376
Welcome. I'm Alice Smith.

01:36.386 --> 01:38.376
Come in.

01:38.386 --> 01:40.556
<i>...you will be happy here.</i>

01:40.636 --> 01:45.176
<i>♪ I'm gonna
spend my life, honey ♪</i>

01:45.256 --> 01:49.016
First off, I'd like to say that this
is a wonderful place to raise a family.

01:49.026 --> 01:52.346
Many a fort were built by my
two girls in this very room.

01:52.426 --> 01:54.216
And bonus.

01:54.296 --> 01:57.076
It's also where my serial killer
father showed us creepy snuff films.

01:57.146 --> 01:59.896
Elizabeth,
shouldn't you be at school?

01:59.906 --> 02:02.566
We have wonderful schools
in this district.

02:02.576 --> 02:04.366
Oh, I see that you're eyeing
the fireplace,

02:04.436 --> 02:05.696
which is original to the house.

02:05.776 --> 02:07.696
Yes, and comes with
fun accessories, like

02:07.776 --> 02:10.666
the shovel my mother used
to knock out my father.

02:10.746 --> 02:12.536
The notorious serial killer.

02:12.616 --> 02:13.576
The Black Hood.

02:13.656 --> 02:15.176
It's true, you can google it.

02:15.246 --> 02:18.876
But make sure you look up Alice
Cooper, and not Alice Smith.

02:18.956 --> 02:21.716
It's all there.
Or try murder house on Elm Street.

02:21.786 --> 02:23.846
It's this house.

02:29.626 --> 02:31.886
Don't they got a gym
at your school?

02:31.966 --> 02:33.886
Is there a problem, Mo?

02:33.966 --> 02:34.896
Yeah.

02:36.276 --> 02:37.656
I need you to start paying dues.

02:39.306 --> 02:40.366
Yeah. No, I get that.

02:41.976 --> 02:44.236
- It's just that...
- Or, you could...

02:44.316 --> 02:46.406
Help out here.
Sweep the place up.

02:46.476 --> 02:48.126
Take the trash out,

02:48.196 --> 02:50.616
- lock up at night.
- Yeah.

02:50.696 --> 02:52.586
That sounds great.
Thank you, Mo.

