03:03.786 --> 03:06.756
Um... Excuse us.

03:06.836 --> 03:08.886
Sorry to interrupt your game...

03:08.956 --> 03:11.716
But this room is reserved for the Farm
from 3:00 to 4:00 every Wednesday.

03:11.796 --> 03:14.896
Not every Wednesday,
you daughter of Manson.

03:14.976 --> 03:16.316
The third Wednesday
of every month is reserved

03:16.396 --> 03:20.226
for monthly Student
Council/LGBTQIA meetings.

03:20.306 --> 03:23.106
I didn't see your name on
Mrs. Bell's activity calendar.

03:23.186 --> 03:26.566
You dare lecture me, your Student Council
President on rules and procedures?

03:26.646 --> 03:29.286
If this were the 18th century,
I'd have you beheaded.

03:29.366 --> 03:31.616
Hey, bitches,

03:31.696 --> 03:33.746
we're in the middle of
a quest here.

03:33.816 --> 03:37.296
Go crawl back to the freak show
from whence you came, you abomination.

03:47.346 --> 03:48.996
Hey, what the hell's going on
over there?

03:48.996 --> 03:51.186
The Gargoyles are mixing it up
with the Poisons and the Farmies.

03:53.046 --> 03:56.356
Is this a high school
or a Roger Cormen movie?

03:57.716 --> 03:59.936
What do you two
have to say for yourselves?

04:00.016 --> 04:02.146
The fight had already started
when we got there, sir.

04:02.226 --> 04:03.936
We were trying to break up
the fight.

04:04.016 --> 04:07.486
Mr. Jones, Ms. Topaz, you're the
leaders of your respective gangs,

04:07.496 --> 04:12.126
but today's brawl is only the most recent
incident of gang activity at Riverdale High.

04:12.196 --> 04:14.336
Someone robbed
the Chemistry lab last night.

04:16.236 --> 04:20.216
- Someone robbed the lab?
- Thousands of dollars of equipment was taken.

04:20.286 --> 04:22.496
All of which could be used
to cook drugs.

04:22.576 --> 04:25.336
The Serpents
don't cook, or steal.

04:25.416 --> 04:27.056
Neither do the Pretty Poisons.

04:30.396 --> 04:32.186
One more strike.

04:33.216 --> 04:34.356
One more strike!

04:36.216 --> 04:38.356
And you're done in my school.

04:40.056 --> 04:42.856
Ooh! All good, boss?

04:42.926 --> 04:44.156
Need me to bounce someone?

04:45.746 --> 04:47.866
Would that it were
so simple, Reggie.

04:49.476 --> 04:51.736
<i>Mija,</i> my guests
would like another round.

04:51.746 --> 04:53.196
Big night for you fellas, huh?

04:53.276 --> 04:55.156
Yeah, important
prospective clients

04:55.166 --> 04:57.196
need to be properly courted.

04:57.206 --> 05:00.086
I see. So, should I be putting all
this on your American Excess, Daddy?

05:00.166 --> 05:02.756
What are you talking about?
These are comped, of course.

05:02.836 --> 05:05.756
Daddy, you've been here for hours.
This is a huge bill.

05:05.836 --> 05:07.296
And you owe me a huge debt.

05:07.366 --> 05:08.516
So, again...

05:09.266 --> 05:10.726
This is comped.

05:15.216 --> 05:16.896
Reggie, man the bar.

05:19.346 --> 05:21.936
How the hell
did we get here, Reggie?

05:21.946 --> 05:25.726
Gladys and my dad are running
roughshod over La Bonne Nuit.

05:25.806 --> 05:30.196
And I don't have any leverage because
I owe them both so much money.

05:30.266 --> 05:34.576
And literally every dollar we make
is going straight into their pockets.

05:34.646 --> 05:36.376
We need a line
on a new cash cow.

05:37.456 --> 05:39.456
Wait. There was one night

05:39.536 --> 05:43.966
when we raked in exponentially
more money than every other night.

05:44.046 --> 05:45.466
The casino night we hosted
with Elio.

05:45.546 --> 05:49.126
- A casino?
- We'd be able to pay off our debts in weeks.

05:49.136 --> 05:50.256
Instead of years.

05:50.326 --> 05:51.926
You think we can pull that off?

05:51.936 --> 05:56.186
I mean, we're already running
a secret speak easy, Reggie.

05:56.886 --> 05:58.356
- Right?
- Right.

06:14.326 --> 06:17.576
What'd they do?
Make you manager?

06:17.646 --> 06:19.286
No, more like janitor.

06:19.356 --> 06:21.056
I'm almost done.

06:21.066 --> 06:22.786
I was thinking maybe we could
grab a bite at Pop's or something?

06:22.866 --> 06:24.676
Perfect. I'm starving.

06:26.846 --> 06:27.966
What is that?

06:45.056 --> 06:46.236
Oh, my God.

06:48.696 --> 06:50.356
What the hell are you
doing in here? Who are you?

06:50.366 --> 06:52.696
Archie, take it easy.

06:52.766 --> 06:55.446
Hey. What's your name?

06:55.516 --> 06:57.626
- Ricky.
- Ricky.

06:58.876 --> 07:01.336
Are... Are you hungry?

07:03.236 --> 07:04.416
Starving.

07:09.296 --> 07:11.876
Uh, so, Ricky...

07:11.886 --> 07:13.546
Where are your parents?

07:13.556 --> 07:16.676
Don't know. Never knew 'em.

07:16.686 --> 07:18.346
How long you been holing up
in that cubby?

07:18.416 --> 07:20.686
On and off for a few weeks.

07:20.766 --> 07:24.806
Ricky, is there anyone
we should call? Any family?

07:24.886 --> 07:26.696
No, I don't have anybody.

07:27.976 --> 07:30.016
Maybe we should try Betty.

07:30.096 --> 07:32.826
She knows people at Social Services.
They would know...

07:33.936 --> 07:36.246
Hey. Ricky! Ricky.

07:36.986 --> 07:39.366
Hey. What's going on?

07:39.436 --> 07:41.736
You... You can't call
Social Services.

07:41.816 --> 07:43.246
- Okay.
- Why not?

07:43.326 --> 07:46.416
Because they send me
to this place, a shelter, okay?

07:46.496 --> 07:47.536
I don't wanna go back.

07:47.616 --> 07:49.626
Okay, what shelter?

07:49.696 --> 07:52.376
The Santa Lucia Shelter.

07:52.456 --> 07:53.926
Did they do something
to you there?

08:01.966 --> 08:03.676
That is the same brand...

08:03.756 --> 08:05.476
I got at Leopold and Loeb, yeah.

08:09.466 --> 08:11.056
All right, Ricky,
who gave you that?

08:11.136 --> 08:12.616
Some older guys at the shelter.

08:12.686 --> 08:14.736
They didn't live there,
but they did crash there, and

08:14.806 --> 08:19.866
one night I woke up, and they were
holding me down and branding my arm.

08:19.936 --> 08:21.916
And that's when
I left the shelter.

